data.enText: very informal words and expressions that are more common in spoken language, especially used by a particular group of people, for example, children, criminals, soldiers, etc.

tr: a characteristic language of a particular group (as among thieves)
informal language consisting of words and expressions that are not considered appropriate for formal occasions
example: their speech was full of slang expressions
The immigrant was duped because he trusted everyone

value.def: Slang consists of words, expressions, and meanings that are informal and are used by people who know each other very well or who have the same interests.

example.ex: Archie liked to think he kept up with current slang.
example.tran: 阿奇喜欢那种紧跟潮流，讲满口时髦新词的感觉。

trans: 同韵俚语(以同韵的词或短语替代另一个词，如伦敦土话中用apples and pears代替stairs)
